<BlogCrossLinks title="Words Starting With NON- — Scrabble Prefix Scoring Guide" />

<p class="text-sm text-gray-500 dark:text-gray-400 mb-6">Published June 15, 2026 · 5 min read</p>

<p class="text-lg leading-relaxed text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-300 mb-8">The NON- prefix means "not" or "absence of" and negates whatever root follows it. While the prefix itself uses only 1-point tiles (N+O+N = 3 points), it creates valid words from roots that otherwise can't take UN- or DIS-. NONSTICK, NONPAREIL, and NONSENSE are all high-frequency Scrabble plays.</p>

<p>NON- is particularly useful in mid-to-late game when you need to extend existing board words for parallel scoring opportunities.</p>

<h2 class="text-xl font-light text-amber-600 dark:text-amber-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-amber-400 pl-4">Why NON- Matters in Scrabble</h2>

<div class="not-prose my-6 p-4 rounded-xl border border-amber-500/30 bg-amber-950/10">
